    "body": "### Problem\n\nHello Friends:\n\nI'm fairly new to `neovim`, but having used `vim(1)` for decades. Thank you for this work and support.\n\nMany users like me have struggled to preserve `pyright`s **intellisense**, **code completion** (etc) enabled, yet disable it's **diagnostic output** (e.g. `PEP8`, `LINTING`, etc) - which can be overwhelming.\n\nHere is a dump of my `neovim` configuration directory:\n\n```\nhttps://github.com/nmvega/neovim-nvchad-python-config\n```\n\nMight someone be kind enough to guide me on how to disable `pyright`s error output ((e.g. `PEP8`, `LINTING`, etc), but without losing code intellisense /  hinting / docstring capability?\n\nI've searched and tried everything I can think of with no luck, so anyone's help would be greatly appreciated. I really wish to move away from `vsCode` but these errors prevent me from doing so.\n\nPS: My installation is based on `NvChad`.\n\nThank you! `=:)`\n\n \n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```\n(pyvenv.d) nmvega@thinkpad$ nvim --version\nNVIM v0.10.4\nBuild type: RelWithDebInfo\nLuaJIT 2.1.1720049189\nRun \"nvim -V1 -v\" for more info\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nDesired behavior is `pyright` but with diagnostic messages suppressed.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.4 Build type: RelWithDebInfo LuaJIT 2.1.1720049189 Run \"nvim -V1 -v\" for more info\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nversion v9.1.1169 works fine. No issues. They are unrelated.\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nFedora-41 / Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nterminator (bit all terminals tried behave the same). It's a \"pyright\" issue.\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nlinux\n\n### Installation\n\nI followed this video, which uses NvChat: https://youtu.be/4BnVeOUeZxc?si=ubwiMO7HZ0HtMy72",
